{"summary":"Accept all four amendments. The duplicate completion-journal replay and paused-state clobber are correctness bugs; the redundant re-collapse and single-use test-lock helper are smaller but still valid maintainability and robustness improvements.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-8-841107a4","decision":"accept","rationale":"`current_bead_runs` is already the result of `latest_task_runs_per_bead`, so passing it to `active_bead_ids` repeats the same per-bead collapse before applying the non-terminal filter. Replacing that call with a direct filter over `current_bead_runs` is semantically equivalent, removes wasted work, and makes the invariant at this call site clearer."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-7e4d3238","decision":"accept","rationale":"The helper’s coordination channels are consumed with `take()`, so only the first `with_milestone_write_lock` call actually signals and blocks; later calls silently skip the contention handshake. That hidden single-use contract can make future concurrency tests pass without exercising the intended lock behavior, so documenting it explicitly, preferably with an assertion, is a worthwhile robustness fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-beaac5f9","decision":"accept","rationale":"This is a real idempotency bug. `update_task_run` intentionally allows replaying an already-finalized attempt to backfill missing metadata, but the completion journal dedupe key includes the serialized `details` field, so adding `plan_hash` or `outcome_detail` changes the key and appends a second `BeadCompleted` or `BeadFailed` event for the same attempt instead of repairing the existing record."},{"amendment_id":"fr-8-3e84cce1","decision":"accept","rationale":"`Paused` is a distinct non-terminal lifecycle state, and the model explicitly supports it. The current reconciliation logic rewrites any non-terminal snapshot with no active bead and prior task history to `Ready`, so replaying lineage during completion repair or backfill can silently clear an operator-imposed pause even though lineage does not contradict that paused state."}]}